{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"707a05cb-974d-488c-99d1-a7c05e969b3e","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **natively**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a bridge for .NET 9 and earlier; it's no longer needed and can be removed.\n\nSince you already have `EnableMSTestRunner` (which builds your test project as an MTP executable), you just need to drop the obsolete property:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01HrwJzoSLpRAaV7F3zLDgY8","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01WP4XMu2T7GaHAotz6BRYrn","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-1a4b2f35c3f3472088376f62f02ed3e8/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n","new_str":""},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-1a4b2f35c3f3472088376f62f02ed3e8/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"791ffb29-b1ac-472c-8dde-9556793d7e8d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) via `EnableMSTestRunner`. They have `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to `true`.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. This property was needed in .NET 9 and earlier to bridge `dotnet test` with MTP-based test projects. In .NET 10, MTP is the default test runner integration, so `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed.\n\n\nI'll walk through the recommended change and update their configuration accordingly.","outputTokens":473,"requestId":"703A:1CDC41:E0755E2:F6AD88F:69F2A8E5"},"id":"b815a199-f7ba-4217-8d2b-e362f6268ece","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:57:17.228Z","parentId":"c8314a50-8a92-4c5b-b6e5-b11306c53a04"}
